  "prompt": "Do men or women have a better orgasm?",
  "response": "The experience of an orgasm is highly subjective and can vary widely from person to person, regardless of gender. There is no definitive way to say whether men or women have \"better\" orgasms, as this involves personal, psychological, and physiological factors. \n\nStudies and anecdotal evidence suggest that women may have the potential for longer and multiple orgasms, while men may experience a refractory period that limits the frequency of orgasms in a short period of time. However, individual experiences will differ, and cultural, emotional, and interpersonal contexts will also play a significant role in the sexual experience.\n\nUltimately, it's important to focus on personal satisfaction and communication with partners to enhance sexual experiences, rather than comparing across genders.",
